#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_panoramasky.rst:19
msgid ""
"A resource referenced in an :ref:`Environment <class_Environment>` that "
"is used to draw a background. The Panorama sky functions similar to "
"skyboxes in other engines, except it uses an equirectangular sky map "
"instead of a cube map."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_panoramasky.rst:21
msgid ""
"Using an HDR panorama is strongly recommended for accurate, high-quality "
"reflections. Godot supports the Radiance HDR (``.hdr``) and OpenEXR "
"(``.exr``) image formats for this purpose."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_panoramasky.rst:23
msgid ""
"You can use `this tool <https://danilw.github.io/GLSL-"
"howto/cubemap_to_panorama_js/cubemap_to_panorama.html>`_ to convert a "
"cube map to an equirectangular sky map."
msgstr ""

